# Windsurf Rules for SvelteKit-NestJS-Turbo

## Project Overview
Full-stack production SvelteKit-NestJS-Turbo with SvelteKit, NestJS, TypeORM, PostgreSQL, and Turborepo.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: SvelteKit + TailwindCSS + Shadcn-Svelte + Melt UI
- **Backend**: NestJS + TypeORM + PostgreSQL + Redis
- **Monorepo**: Turborepo
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)

## Structure
```
apps/
  web/          # SvelteKit app (port 3002)
  api/          # NestJS API (port 3001)
packages/
  types/        # Shared TS types
  config/       # ESLint & Prettier
  ui/           # Shared components (future)
  database/     # Shared entities (future)
```

## Development
```bash
npm run dev                                        # All apps
npm run dev --workspace=web                        # Frontend only
npm run dev --workspace=api                        # Backend only
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d     # Start databases
```

## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- No `any` types
- Prefer `const`, async/await
- Functions < 50 lines

### File Naming
- Source files: `kebab-case.ts`
- Components: `PascalCase.svelte`
- Functions: `camelCase()`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

### Svelte Component Structure
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  // 1. Imports
  // 2. Props (export let)
  // 3. State
  // 4. Reactive ($:)
  // 5. Functions
  // 6. Lifecycle
</script>

<!-- HTML with TailwindCSS -->
<style>/* Scoped styles if needed */</style>
```

### NestJS Patterns
- Use decorators consistently
- DTOs with class-validator
- Swagger on all endpoints
- Proper DI

## Common Tasks

### Add API Endpoint
```bash
cd apps/api && npx nest g resource modules/[name]
```

### Add Frontend Route
Create `apps/web/src/routes/[name]/+page.svelte`

### Add Shared Type
Edit `packages/types/index.ts`

### Database Migration
```bash
cd apps/api && npm run typeorm migration:create src/migrations/[Name]
```

## Configuration
- Database: localhost:5433 (PostgreSQL), localhost:6379 (Redis)
- Environment: apps/api/.env
- TypeScript: Strict mode across all packages

## Styling
- TailwindCSS utilities first
- Use `cn()` helper for conditional classes
- Shadcn-Svelte for UI components
- Melt UI for headless primitives

## Security Checklist
- Validate all inputs
- Use parameterized queries
- Keep secrets in .env
- Sanitize production errors
- Enable CORS selectively

## Testing
- Unit: Vitest
- E2E: Playwright
- Run before committing

## Component Libraries
- **Shadcn-Svelte**: https://shadcn-svelte.com (copy-paste)
- **Melt UI**: https://melt-ui.com (headless)

## Before Coding
1. Read existing patterns
2. Check dependencies
3. Match style
4. Test locally
5. Update docs if needed

## Priorities
1. Type safety
2. Consistency
3. Simplicity
4. Developer experience

## Avoid
- `any` types
- Committing secrets
- Breaking existing patterns
- Adding deps without checking alternatives
